Do you want to play a tabletop rpg? Are you unable to afford(or too lazy to find) the necessary 2-sided, 3-sided, 6-sided, 20-sided, and 1024-sided perfectly balanced dice and the rpg's structure-providing rulebooks and expansions? Here's something I made to help gamemasters make these decisions without any dice, ignoring the structure that mandates dice. Just have the participants fill out the provided character sheets on separate tabs in your browser, and leave the rest to this webpage. It includes generic stat-based dice-rolls for attack, defense, stealth, creating illusions, and doing difficult things. Other features allow players to equip and unequip stat-changing items.

Thanks #anglularjs for making this possible.
